'''Soul Pact''' is a [[Seasonal Mechanic]] introduced in [[Thorns of Devotion]].

==Rules==
# Soul Pact is featured in {{b|selected game modes}} during the [[Thorns of Devotion]], [[Tower of Memory]] and [[Crown of Ashes]] seasons. This feature allows Magisters to deploy {{b|3}} heroes from the same faction to activate that faction's Phantimal. Deploying {{b|3}} Celestial or Hypogean heroes will activate the Celestial & Hypogean Faction Phantimal.
# During the preparation phase, Magisters can adjust the positions of the active Phantimal. Once battle begins, the active Phantimal will {{b|fight alongside the player}}.
# After upgrading a  Phantimal to a certain level, it can designate an ally behind it as the {{b|spirit-marked hero}}, granting them powerful bonuses in battle.
# A Phantimal's stats are determined by the {{b|levels and tiers}} of the deployed heroes.
# In game modes where Soul Pact is active, the player activated Phantimals will gain bonus ATK and HP depending on how many Dimensional heroes they have on the battlefield.

==Phantimal Upgrades & Ascensions==
# Magisters can use upgrade materials to level up their Phantimals, enhancing their stats and skills. Phantimals' upgrade progress {{b|resets}} at the end of each season.
# Resetting a Phantimal returns all materials used. Players can reset Phantimals for free once every {{b|3 days}} or use [[Phantimal Reshapers]] when a free reset is unavailable.

